<%#
  ComingSoonBadge: pre-launch pill shown next to the wordmark on every page while
  Stablemate is in early access. For anonymous visitors it links to sign-up,
  which already branches to the waitlist form once Signup.at_capacity? (see
  RegistrationsController#new). Signed-in visitors get the same pill as plain
  text, never a sign_up_path link — an existing account never gets a sign-up
  CTA (see PagesControllerTest's "never sees sign-up CTAs" coverage).

  Tailwind-styled, for the authenticated app + signed-out auth screens (they
  share `layouts/application`'s tokens). The marketing landing/pricing nav has
  its own `.lp`-scoped equivalent (`.badge-soon` in landing.css, `pages/_nav`)
  so Tailwind classes don't leak into that deliberately isolated design system.
%>
<% badge_classes = "inline-flex items-center h-[20px] px-2 rounded-full bg-brand-tint text-brand-hover " \
                    "text-[10px] font-mono font-semibold uppercase tracking-wide" %>
<% if authenticated? %>
  <span class="<%= badge_classes %>" data-testid="coming-soon-badge">Coming soon</span>
<% else %>
  <%= link_to "Coming soon", sign_up_path,
        class: "#{badge_classes} hover:bg-brand/15",
        data: { testid: "coming-soon-badge" } %>
<% end %>
